===Etymology===
Hebrew [[אבשלום|אַבְשָׁלוֹם]] (Avšalom), "father of peace", from [[אב|אָב]] (av = 'father') + [[שלום|שָׁלוֹם]] (shalom = 'peace').

===Proper noun===
'''Absalom'''
#''{Bible)'' The third [[son]] of [[David]], king of [[Israel]].
# A male [[given name]].

